g.text: This Image shows the array of information an individual may own. From this base level of acknowledging intellectual property, and the ability for users to set-permissions and share that data in an array of different situations or business cases; a number of business cases have been

provided. The Business cases show an instance of community contribution, of legal due-process and the availability of important information relating to a case; the ability for an individual to have secure, yet effective healthcare records and related management processes,

as well as the capacity to using linked-data, to assist in the management of "intangible intellectual property" relating to a "startup" or in the creation of a new content asset; such as a film, by both creating new content as an individual as well as working with other peoples
and organisational contributions as part of the sequence of overall content used to create a new content asset.

Web 3.0 applications, in term of the OSI Networking Layers; use an array of different open-standards based standards to "get going". Whilst this does not reflect the vast array of different implementations that are possible, the basic concept is expressed in that format.

The Web 3.0 performs tasks that recognise social concepts such as individuals contributions to things greater than what they are capable of as an individual alone and the means in which sociologically, these tasks are carried out with others through implied or explicit agreements.

Perhaps meaningfully; in the legal case; often an array of related parties hold information (perhaps in publicly funded departments, and other organisations funded by government) where anysuch information is not ordinarily made available to a judge who is required to make a decision

on the day with the information available before the honourable member of the community, facilitating that role. Through the application of "permissions"; these facilitations can be provided in-full, free from removal or "cherry picking", which in-turn assists the community in upholding
the rule of law, and the spirit of our democracy.
